         <section type="subsection">
          <title>The meaning of <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> values</title>
	  <shortcode>ESCBB</shortcode>
	  <para>The formula for <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> has:</para>
	  <list list-type="bulleted">
	    <item>
	      <para>the concentration of the products in the numerator and the concentration of reactants in the denominator</para>
	    </item>
	    <item>
	      <para>a <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> value <latex>\textcolor{red}{\textbf{greater than 1}}</latex> means that the equilibrium lies <emphasis effect="bold">to the right</emphasis></para>
	      <para><latex>\textcolor{red}{\textbf{there are more products than reactants}}</latex></para>
	    </item>
	    <item>
	      <para>a <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> value <latex>\textcolor{blue}{\textbf{between 0 and 1}}</latex> means that the equilibrium lies <emphasis effect="bold">to the left</emphasis></para>
	      <para><latex>\textcolor{blue}{\textbf{more reactants than products}}</latex></para>
	    </item>
	  </list>
	  <para>This has been summarised in Table <link target-id="fig:tab:Kcval"/>. Note that <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> cannot be 0 or less.</para>
	  <para>Yield describes the quantity of product in the container relative to the maximum product possible.</para>
	  <figure id="fig:tab:Kcval">
	    <type>table</type>
	    <table>
	      <tgroup cols="3">
		<colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
		<colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
		<colspec colnum="3" colname="c3"/>
		<tbody>
		  <row>
		    <entry>
		      <para><emphasis effect="bold"><chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> value</emphasis></para>
		    </entry>
		    <entry>
		      <para><emphasis effect="bold">Equilibrium</emphasis></para>
		    </entry>
		    <entry>
		      <para><emphasis effect="bold">Yield</emphasis></para>
		    </entry>
		  </row>
		  <row>
		    <entry>
		      <para><latex>\textcolor{red}{\text{K}_{\text{c}} &gt; 1}</latex></para>
		    </entry>
		    <entry>
		      <para><latex>\textcolor{red}{\text{to the right}}</latex></para>
		    </entry>
		    <entry>
		      <para><latex>\textcolor{red}{\textbf{more products}}</latex> than reactants</para>
		    </entry>
		  </row>
		  <row>
		    <entry>
		      <para><latex>\textcolor{blue}{0 &lt;\text{K}_{\text{c}}&lt; 1}</latex></para>
		    </entry>
		    <entry>
		      <para><latex>\textcolor{blue}{\text{to the left}}</latex></para>
		    </entry>
		    <entry>
		      <para><latex>\textcolor{blue}{\textbf{more reactants}}</latex> than products</para>
		    </entry>
		  </row>
		</tbody>
	      </tgroup>
	    </table>
	    <caption>
	      <para>The meaning of <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> values.</para>
	    </caption>
	  </figure>
	  <para>A <emphasis effect="bold">high <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound></emphasis> value means that:</para>
	  <list list-type="bulleted">
	    <item>
	      <para>the concentration of products is high</para>
	    </item>
	    <item>
	      <para>the equilibrium lies far to the right</para>
	    </item>
	    <item>
	      <para>the reaction has a <emphasis effect="bold">high yield</emphasis></para>
	    </item>
	  </list>
	  <para>A <emphasis effect="bold">low <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> value</emphasis> (close to 0) means that:</para>
	  <list list-type="bulleted">
	    <item>
	      <para>the concentration of reactants is high</para>
	    </item>
	    <item>
	      <para>the equilibrium lies far to the left</para>
	    </item>
	    <item>
	      <para>the reaction has a <emphasis effect="bold">low yield</emphasis></para>
	    </item>
	  </list>
	</section>
