	      <shortcode>01q4</shortcode>
	      <problem>
              <para>The following reaction takes place:</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>Fe^{3+}(aq) + 4Cl^{-}(aq)</chem_compound> <latex>⇌</latex> <chem_compound>FeCl_{4}^{-}(aq)</chem_compound></para>
              <para><chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> for the reaction is <number><coeff>7.5</coeff><exp>-2</exp></number>. At equilibrium, the concentration of <chem_compound>FeCl^{-}_{4}(aq)</chem_compound>  is <unit_number><number><coeff>0.95</coeff><exp>-4</exp></number><unit>mol.dm<sup>-3</sup></unit></unit_number> and the concentration of free iron <chem_compound>(Fe^{3+}(aq))</chem_compound> is <unit_number><number>0.2</number><unit>mol.dm<sup>-3</sup></unit></unit_number>. Calculate the concentration of chloride ions at equilibrium.</para>
            </problem>
            <solution>
	      <para>We know the value of <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> and the concentration of two of the three substances at equilibrium. So we use the expression for <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> to find the concentration of chloride ions.</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>FeCl_{4}^{-}(aq)</chem_compound> is the product and has a coefficient of <number>1</number>.</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>Fe^{3+}(aq)</chem_compound> is a reactant and has a coefficient of <number>1</number>.</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>Cl^{-}(aq)</chem_compound> is a reactant and has a coefficient of <number>4</number>.</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> <latex>= \dfrac{\text{[FeCl}_{4}^{-}{\text{]}}}{\text{[Fe}^{3+}{\text{][Cl}^{-}\text{]}^{4}}}</latex></para>
	      <para><chem_compound>[Cl^{-}]^{4}</chem_compound> <latex>= \dfrac{\text{[FeCl}_{4}^{-}{\text{]}}}{\text{[Fe}^{3+}{\text{][K}_{\text{c}}\text{]}^{4}}}</latex></para>
	      <para><chem_compound>[Cl^{-}]^{4}</chem_compound> <latex>= \dfrac{<number><coeff>0.95</coeff><exp>-4</exp></number>}{(<number>0.2</number>)(<number><coeff>7.5</coeff><exp>-2</exp></number>)}</latex> = <number>0.0063</number></para>
	      <para><chem_compound>[Cl^{-}] = </chem_compound><correct><unit_number><number>0.28</number><unit>mol.dm<sup>-3</sup></unit></unit_number></correct></para>
	    </solution>
