	    </code>
	  </pspicture>
	  <para>If you <emphasis effect="bold">increase</emphasis> the pressure (shown by a decrease in volume), the equilibrium will shift to <emphasis effect="bold">decrease</emphasis> the number of gas molecules. That shift is to the right and the number of <chem_compound>H_{2}</chem_compound> and <chem_compound>N_{2}</chem_compound> molecules will decrease while the number of <chem_compound>NH_{3}</chem_compound> molecules will increase:</para>
	  <pspicture>
	    <code>
	      (-0.6,-0.5)(13,0.5)
	      \newrgbcolor{skyblue}{0.33 0.41 1}
	      \rput(-0.3,0){\textbf{(b)}}
	      \rput(1,0){\text{{\skyblue 3H$_{2}$} + {\blue 1N$_{2}$}}}
	      \psline(2.1,0.04)(2.7,0.04)
	      \psline(2.7,0.04)(2.6,0.13)
	      \psline(2.1,-0.04)(2.4,-0.04)
	      \psline(2.1,-0.04)(2.2,-0.13)
	      \rput(3.3,0){\text{\red 6NH$_{3}$}}
