		      <title>Write an expression for the equilibrium constant of this reaction and calculate <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound>.</title>
		      
		      <para><latex>\text{K}_{\text{c}} = \dfrac{\text{[COCl}_{2}{\text{]}}}{\text{[CO][Cl}_{2}{\text{]}}}</latex></para>
		      <para><latex>\text{K}_{\text{c}} = \dfrac{<number>0.75</number>}{(<number>1.75</number>)(<number>0.6</number>)} = </latex> <number>0.71</number></para>
		    </workstep>
		    <workstep>
		      <title>What happens at t = <unit_number><number>20</number><unit>s</unit></unit_number>?</title>
		      
		      <para>The concentration of <chem_compound>CO</chem_compound> increases sharply. The concentrations of the other compounds do not change dramatically. Therefore <chem_compound>CO</chem_compound> must have been added to the system.</para>
		      <para>After this addition of <chem_compound>CO</chem_compound> there is a shift to reduce the amount of <chem_compound>CO</chem_compound>, that is in the forward direction. Therefore the concentration of the product increases while the concentrations of the reactants decrease.</para>
		    </workstep>
		    <workstep>
