	      <problem>
              <para>The following reaction has reached equilibrium in a closed container:</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>C(s) + H_{2}O(g)</chem_compound> <latex>⇌</latex> <chem_compound>CO(g) + H_{2}(g)</chem_compound> <latex>\phantom{\rule{28.45274pt}{0ex}}\Delta{H} &gt;</latex> 0</para>
              <para>The pressure of the system is then decreased. How will the concentration of the <chem_compound>H_{2}</chem_compound> (g) and the value of <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> be affected when the new equilibrium is established? Assume that the temperature of the system remains unchanged.</para>
	      <para>.</para>
	      <table>
