	    <entry>
	      <problem>
		<para>Calculate the concentration of each of the reactants and the product using figures from the graph between <unit_number><number>5</number><unit>minutes</unit></unit_number> and <unit_number><number>10</number><unit>minutes</unit></unit_number> and hence calculate the equilibrium constant <chem_compound>K_{c}</chem_compound> for this reaction at <unit_number><number>298</number><unit>K</unit></unit_number></para>
	      </problem>
	      <solution>
		<para>The concentration values are read off the graph.</para>
		<para>C(<chem_compound>A_{2}</chem_compound>) <latex>= \dfrac{<unit_number><number>2.0</number><unit>mol</unit></unit_number>}{<unit_number><number>2</number><unit>dm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number>} = </latex> <unit_number><number>1.0</number><unit>mol.dm<sup>-3</sup></unit></unit_number></para>
		<para>C(<chem_compound>B_{2}</chem_compound>) <latex>= \dfrac{<unit_number><number>1.2</number><unit>mol</unit></unit_number>}{<unit_number><number>2</number><unit>dm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number>} = </latex> <unit_number><number>0.6</number><unit>mol.dm<sup>-3</sup></unit></unit_number></para>
		<para>C(<chem_compound>AB_{2}</chem_compound>) <latex>= \dfrac{<unit_number><number>0.8</number><unit>mol</unit></unit_number>}{<unit_number><number>2</number><unit>dm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number>} = </latex> <unit_number><number>0.4</number><unit>mol.dm<sup>-3</sup></unit></unit_number></para>	
		<para><latex>\text{K}_{\text{c}} = \dfrac{\text{[AB}_{2}{\text{]}}^{2}}{\text{[A}_{2}{\text{][B}_{2}{\text{]}}^{2}}} = \dfrac{<number>0.4</number>^{2}}{(<number>1.0</number>)(<number>0.6</number>)^{2}} = </latex> <correct><number>0.44</number></correct></para>
